verbose_text: Of note, the association of TLR7 expression with other members of the pathway like MYD88 or JMJD3 (r = 0.361, P = 0.017; and r = 0.341, P = 0.022, respectively) was not as powerful as that found with TLR2, which may indicate that TLR7 upregulation is not necessarily related to increased signaling towards NF-kappaB activation.
